page.title: 04 CUBBINGTON
page.content: {Cubbington}is quite an old village. It has just eight shops which include two groceries, a post office, an off license, a fish & chip shop, a butcher, a chemist and hairdressers On the way to the shops there is a church called St Marys.It is nice.I often go there with the guides. The guides is held in a village hall. I live in a new building site called Pinehurst. Pinehurst is just up from a sawmill. There are two sawmills in Cubbington The main wood the sawmill has is pine but they also have oak, ash and deciduous. There is a lot of land in Cubbington. Most of it is crops, there is some land for cattle. We have a restaurant called The Rugby Tavern which is on the Rugby Road.The Rugby Road joins up with Cubbington Road which leads to Lillington.
